title: Anyone know this one...?
content:
Trying to do a DIY project and would love to know this font. Can anyone help?  
Thanks in advance.

comments.content: Look close to **[Bou College](http://web.archive.org/web/20130819051714/http:/www.findmyfont.com/index.php/fonts/font-preview?fset=Dafont-1&ffam=Bou%20College%20-%20Regular&fid=636c99a22a09767ab9afd1fb425b20de&fsize=60&text=CREME%20DE%20LA%20CREME&fit=1)** free font by Agustín Bou

Edit: Found also Bou but too late. So to make this post "a bit less useless", here are some more in the same vein: [United Sans](http://web.archive.org/web/20130819051714/http:/www.houseind.com/fonts/unitedcollection), [Hoboken Sans](http://web.archive.org/web/20130819051714/http:/lineto.com/The+Fonts/Font+Categories/Headline+Fonts/Hoboken+High/Sans+Serif/), [Octin College](http://web.archive.org/web/20130819051714/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/typodermic/octin-college/), [Liberator](http://web.archive.org/web/20130819051714/http:/www.losttype.com/font/?name=liberator), [Haymaker](http://web.archive.org/web/20130819051714/http:/www.losttype.com/font/?name=haymaker) (Tuscan median spurred), [Pop Warner](http://web.archive.org/web/20130819051714/http:/www.dafont.com/pop-warner.font), [Jefferies Jaynz](http://web.archive.org/web/20130819051714/http:/www.dafont.com/jefferies-jaynz.font),
